SR:
I encountered a MissingResourceException when trying to create an instance of the FontRegistry class for my application. The code I used is as follows:

com.company.product.MyClass
public void createFontRegistry(){
    FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}

I have a file named fonts.properties in the com/company/product folder. However, when I try the following code instead:

com.company.product.MyClass
public void createFontRegistry(){
    ResourceBundle fonts = ResourceBundle.getBundle("com.company.product.fonts");
}

No exception is thrown. Additionally, if I create a complete copy of the FontRegistry class in my com.company.product package, it works. This leads me to believe that there is a bug in the FontRegistry class.
